<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06156a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06156a">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06156a"> 156(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> lake which burneth with fire / hate brother = murderer</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">SIXTH COMMANDMENT. &ldquo;THOU SHALT DO NO MURDER.&rdquo; <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> This command also forbids anger, &ldquo;hatred, and malice, and all uncharitableness.&rdquo; St. John says &ldquo;<mark>Whosoever hateth his brother is a murderer</mark>.&rdquo; The portion of the murderer is in &ldquo;<mark>the lake which burneth with fire</mark> and brimstone.&rdquo; <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 37</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
